Function: stringStream()

  stringStream (  options  ,  cb  ):  Writable 

Defined in: src/index.ts:138

Creates a stream that parses a sequence of strings into a document.

The stream is a  Writable  stream that accepts strings. When the stream is finished, the callback is
called with the loaded document.

Parameters <L=l#2></L><I=2>
options <L=l#3></L><I=3>
<L=n> CheerioOptions </L>

The options to pass to Cheerio.

cb <L=l#4></L><I=4>
(  err  ,  $  ) =>  void 

The callback to call when the stream is finished.

Returns <L=l#5></L><I=5>
 Writable 

The writable stream.

Example <L=l#6></L><I=6>
```javascript
import * as cheerio from 'cheerio';
import * as fs from 'fs';

const writeStream = cheerio.stringStream({}, (err, $) => {
  if (err) {
    // Handle error
  }

  console.log($('h1').text());
  // Output: Hello, world!
});

fs.createReadStream('my-document.html', { encoding: 'utf8' }).pipe(
  writeStream,
);
```

[] []
</B>
