<L=e> Cheerio </L> <  S  extends <L=v> SelectorType </L> ?  Element  :  T  >

Example <L=m#a></L><I=a>
```javascript
$('ul .pear').attr('class');
//=> pear

$('li[class=orange]').html();
//=> Orange

$('.apple', '#fruits').text();
//=> Apple
```

[] []

Optionally, you can also load HTML by passing the string as the selector:

```javascript
$('<ul id="fruits">...</ul>');
```

[] []

Or the context:

```javascript
$('ul', '<ul id="fruits">...</ul>');
```

[] []

Or as the root:

```javascript
$('li', 'ul', '<ul id="fruits">...</ul>');
```

[] []

