sourceCodeLocationInfo? <L=n#g></L><I=g>
   optional  sourceCodeLocationInfo :  boolean 

Defined in: node_modules/parse5/dist/parser/index.d.ts:51

Enables source code location information. When enabled, each node (except the root node) will have a
 sourceCodeLocation  property. If the node is not an empty element,  sourceCodeLocation  will be a
ElementLocation object, otherwise it will be Location . If the element was implicitly created by the
parser (as part of tree correction ), its  sourceCodeLocation  property will be  undefined  .

Default <L=n#h></L><I=h>
 false 

